				\begin{document}$${{\varPhi }}_{\text{e}} = \frac{{{{\varPhi }}_{\text{v}} }}{{\sum_{380nm}^{780nm} K_m \times V\left( \lambda \right) \times S\left( \lambda \right)}},$$\end{document}with ϕv given in the specific datasheet. Subsequently, ϕe(λ) was calculated by multiplying the relative spectral power distribution S(λ) for each wavelength with the formerly calculated total physical luminous flux of the illuminant.

For the calculation of photosynthetically active quanta, the photonic energy per wavelength was calculated as:7E=ϕ×hcλ,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
