				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$E = \phi \times \frac{hc}{\lambda },$$\end{document}where h is the Planck constant and c is the speed of light. The number of quanta per wavelength was calculated by dividing the numerical values of the power distribution for each wavelength by the dedicated photonic energy. Finally, the number of photosynthetically active quanta was calculated by integrating all photons between 400 and 700 nm.
